reviews.review_text:
Major Truckin'/ Major Phil Lot's of rumblin' Leshtastic bass on this one. A very good recording in general.  The set list is kinda loopy. 
Truckin' is one of the best rocked out versions I've heard. Watch out! It's real all-timer. IMHO.
The rest of the show doesn't quite rise to the same level. There's kinda on off-kilter/shifty vibe to this show.  Very interesting. Play it loud on big speakers.
yep Best Truckin' ever.  Not on anyone's radar (or in teh books/reviews), too...

killer show qs recording one of the best CRS openers ever BUT where's the dynamics - no sweat I recorded it in 79 off of masters but have no masters or copies (well one eroded one)  ouch! better copies must exist for sure! I hope - best double clutch by weir coming out of the jam in cold rain serious!!! - i was 10 feet away! kkkblam ,kkkblam!

the sb recordings dont get it!!! ha love!

Brent's show? I get a groove of Brent throughout this show.
It's pretty cool.  I wouldn't have found it, Sirius played it tonite.  Catch it.
